abstracts.cdata!:
This note concerns the Sixth Banque
            Nationale pour le Developpement Economique Project (BNDE VI
            Project) for Morocco. The project was approved on May 8,
            1973, became effective on September 10, 1973, and closed on
            March 31, 1977. A Project Completion Report was not prepared
            after project completion. Instead, the project was included
            into a later case study by the Operations Evaluation
            Department (OED) covering the history of the relationship
            between BNDE and the Bank Group during the 1970s and beyond.
            That study is entitled "The Sustainability of
            Development Finance Institutions in an Evolutionary
            Environment" (Report Number 7658). This note also lists
            several other Project Performance Audit Reports which cover
            previous and subsequent Bank loans to BNDE.
